cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.IT, cs.AI, cs.LG 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with perceptual image quality assessment. Additionally, it may also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category as it deals with image quality assessment. Information Theory (cs.IT) is also a likely sub-category as the paper discusses different pooling strategies for IQA models. Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) are also possible sub-categories as the paper proposes a new pooling strategy and compares it with existing ones, which is a common theme in these sub-categories.
